UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=4354; /* Text0_1: Greetings, $c. Don\'t have too much time to talk--I\'m just using Chillwind as a camp to get some rest before heading to Hearthglen. I\'ve heard word that before they went crazy, the Scarlet Crusade had a mage working for them who was trying to create powerful bows and guns for their soldiers. I\'m not sure if he succeeded or not... the Crusade killed him before any of his finished product made it out. Maybe they killed him to keep it a secret... or maybe they distrust the arcane that much. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=4355; /* Text0_1: He... hello, $N. Sorry, I\'m recovering from my wounds.$B$BThose Scarlet Crusaders are tougher than I had given them credit for. They almost did me in.$B$BYou should be careful too. I\'d hate to see them get the jump on you. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=4356; /* Text0_1: My family worked  the Northridge Lumber Mill in what\'s now Western Plaguelands. They were dedicated to the Dumah family, and now the Scarlet Crusade have taken it over along with all of Hearthglen!$B$BI will not rest until those zealots are wiped from Azeroth. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc6='Long ago, before the last great war, my father ran the Northridge Lumber Mill. It was his life, and he was committed to it. Then the war came, and as much as it pained him, we had to flee to Stormwind.$B$BWe lost a number of friends and family in the those days, and it pains me to know that the Scarlet Crusade has taken the mill for their own ends.$B$BThat\'s why I\'ve returned.' WHERE entry=4357; /* Text0_0: Long ago, before the last great war, my father ran the Northridge Lumber Mill. It was his life, and he was committed to it. Then the war came, and as much as it pained him, we had to flee to Stormwind.$B$BWe lost a number of friends and family in the those days, and it pains me to know that the Scarlet Crusade has taken the mill for their own ends.$B$BThat\'s why I\'ve returned. */
