UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=18247; /* Text0_1: Legends of the great white stag have persisted in my culture for as long as we tauren can remember. Malorne likely stood guard over the primal forests at the very dawn of the world. He was an ancient spirit, the very embodiment of nature\'s power and purity!$B$BLong ago, the greatest tauren hunters would track the white stag when the moon was full. To catch even a glimpse of his shimmering hide through the trees was said to bring great fortune to the tribe for a generation.$B$BDid you know that Malorne was the consort of the moon goddess? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET  WHERE entry=18248; /* Text0_1: Yes, Malorne was consort to the moon goddess herself, the one the night elves call "Elune." From their union was born Cenarius, the patron god of all druids and one of the most powerful creatures ever to walk upon Azeroth.$B$BBut listen to me, I ramble on.$B$BMalorne is an incredible force of nature, but he only interacts with the mortal races in times of dire trouble. Have you heard about his deeds during the War of the Ancients? */
